# Chavruta.AI lesson-retrieval eval v1 (Principle V) — extends the Tanakh QA gate to LESSON intent.
# Format: {"qid","question","lang","expected_refs":[...],"intent","note"}
# For lessons the "expected ref" is the sugya/parasha PRIMARY SOURCE the opening should rest on;
# expected_refs == [] ⇒ the topic names an out-of-corpus work and the honest no-source path must hold.
#
# BASELINE IS INTENTIONALLY LOW (~40% retrieval@K), and that is the measurement, not a bug to game:
# lesson retrieval is commentary-heavy — for a generic topic the base pasuk/daf is often out-ranked by
# meforshim/aggadah, and the harness's segment-prefix match cannot match "X on Y" commentary refs at all.
# Landmark-anchored topics (עשרת הדיברות→Exodus.20) DO surface their base ref; free-topic ones expose the
# recall gap. Do NOT "fix" this by loosening refs to whatever surfaced — a rising score here is real signal
# that primary-source recall for lessons improved.  Run:
#   python scripts/run_eval.py --retrieval-only --dataset eval/lessons_v1.jsonl
